      "comment": "THE ART OF SUCCESS (1) faces her toughest test yet but she is a mare on the up having put four wins together, the last two at this venue when she worked from back row draws but proved too good. The inside barrier gives her the chance to take this next step. SWEET IDEAL (9) found winning form when second-up in a higher-graded race two back at this venue then drew on this row and settled back but worked home well to place. Race fit and will be hard to hold out if things go her way. TOORAM MAGIC (3) was runner-up from the back line last time and won two of his previous three starts, one of them here. Must be considered from a good draw. LE BELLE BIJOUX (8) is an each way hope.",
